*SIEVE
REM: PILOT has limited array/loop support - this demos the concept
T: Sieve of Eratosthenes
T: Finding primes up to 30 by trial division
T: (PILOT lacks arrays, using explicit checks)
T: 
C: N=2
*LOOP
C: ISPRIME=1
C: D=2
*INNER
C: SQ=D*D
JY(*NEXTD): SQ>N
C: R=N-(N/D)*D
JN(*NOTPRIME): R#0
C: ISPRIME=0
*NOTPRIME
*NEXTD
C: D=D+1
JY(*INNER): D<N
JN(*SKIP): ISPRIME#1
T: #N is prime
*SKIP
C: N=N+1
JY(*LOOP): N<=30
T: Done.
E:
